Control mostly clear with one Balsam tree inthe river just down from gauge.  May or maynot have "B" affect. BM tie on May 24 2012 showed NO05005 as being -.009 low.  This BM is thought to have been driven on with the truck on this day and the tied in elevation is used today to compute DWL and MGH.  There have been previous level ties to this BM and they tied in high but are also tagged as suspect.  Two new BM's will have to be installed and in the meantime only the Master BM should be used as it is cemented in bedrock downstream of the gauge. Sources:Manual
